Done. Built **`kb`** — a terminal Kanban board in Go.

### What it does

**CLI commands:**
- `kb` — opens interactive TUI board (vim keys, column navigation, drag tasks between columns)
- `kb add "title" -p high -t tag1,tag2` — create tasks with priority and tags
- `kb list [column]` — view board in terminal
- `kb start <id>` / `kb done <id>` — quick status changes
- `kb move <id> <column>` — move to any column
- `kb delete <id>` — remove tasks

**Interactive TUI** (bubbletea):
- 3-column Kanban layout (To Do / In Progress / Done)
- `h/l` navigate columns, `j/k` navigate tasks
- `H/L` move tasks between columns
- `+/-` change priority, `d` delete, `?` help
- Color-coded priorities, tag display, strikethrough for done items

**Storage:** Single `.kb.json` file in the current directory (override with `KB_FILE` env var).

**Tests:** 10 tests covering model operations and persistence. All passing.
